When 2 people each have to write a lot
of  articles,  some  points tend to be
the  same  in  those articles, and the
general  theme  in  what  they  write,
tends  to  come to the light.  I mean,
after  15 articles on the scene by one
person,  in  one  mag, one must notice
some  similarities.   That is also the
case  here,  and  the overall theme of
»CL6:Devotion»CL1:,   shining   through,   is  a
problematic  one,  I think.  Now, »CL2:Wade»CL1:
and»CL2: Sane»CL1: are old sceners, and I really
mean  old  sceners,  who have followed
the  scene since the »CL0:A500 demos»CL1:.  This
tends  to  make  you  somewhat  biased
towards   »CL0:newer»CL1:   things,  you  get  a
certain »CL0: conservative»CL1:  outlook.  And I
know  this,  since I thought I was the
most conservative scener active today,
heh   (you  should  just  look  at  my
votingsheet..     Or..     Maybe   you
shouldn't...).  After reading »CL6:Devotion
#2»CL1:, I'm not so sure anymore.  Clearly,
the  interests  of both, but it shines
most   clearly   through   in  »CL2: Sane's»CL1:
article,  is  the  old  scene, the old
legends,  how it was once upon a time,
how  the  grass was »CL3:greener»CL1:, the birds
