the  merits  of  the  past  time,  and
writing articles about how the present
sucks,  when  it  is  the present that
counts  right now.  It is »CL0:demotivating»CL1:
and  it  »CL0:destroys»CL1: rather than»CL0: creates.»CL1:
We must make do with what we have now,
look  to  the  past with nostalgia and
try  to  learn  a  few  things, but we
should  not  wish back the past, or be
too  unhappy  with  what  we have now.
What  we have now is also good, albeit
different  from what once was.  In any
case, it has no place »CL0:alienating»CL1: newer
sceners   with   this,   it   is   not
constructive,  and  again,  I guess it
